				<outline text="Idea: The Web Corps" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 17:24:47 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Something that would be cool is a group of people who transplant items from inside silos like Facebook and make them accessible from the rest of the web." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 17:24:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I just asked Lisa Williams to post one of her items on a blog, usually I don't, because it gets people upset. I was going to ask Enoch Choi also because I know he believes in the web, but he's busy, and the web stuff is probably very tangential to what he's doing right now." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 17:25:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Think of it as a Web Corps. Very simple, transplant stuff outside Facebook so it can be accessed everywhere." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 20:02:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Update: Lisa posted her item on &lt;a href=&quot;https://lisawilliams.github.io/lisa/tech/2017/08/28/Hurricane-Harvey-Senior-Tracker.html&quot;&gt;her blog&lt;/a&gt; (she was already working on it when I asked) and I transplanted Enoch's post &lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/transplants/enoch.opml&quot;&gt;on this.how&lt;/a&gt;. So we're up and running. There's no &quot;official&quot; place to transplant to, as long as it has a URL that's publicly accessible. ;-) " created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 20:02:09 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Burner news" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:07:09 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="This is for my lovely friend &lt;a href=&quot;http://nakedjen.com/&quot;&gt;nakedjen&lt;/a&gt; when she returns from Burning Man." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:07:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/burnerNews/&quot;&gt;http://this.how/burnerNews/&lt;/a&gt;" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:07:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's a log of only the most important events that have happened while she is on the playa."/>
					<outline text="It's been a very interesting exercise for me, the idea of recording only the most important news, the stuff a person at Burning Man needs to know about when they return." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:07:41 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I did not include, for example, the end of Season 7 of Game of Thrones, even though it's very consequential for some. It's not urgent. Hurricane Harvey and the pardon of Joe Arpaio are essential news. And North Korea launching a missile over Japan." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:07:54 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I feel great!" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:25:17 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;iframe width=&quot;374&quot; height=&quot;158&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/XbFLhbJRt_E&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:25:21 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 28" created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 15:18:58 GMT" name="28">
				<outline text="The &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.berkeleyside.com/2017/08/28/berkeley-community-comes-force-hate-racism/&quot;&gt;Berkeleyside report&lt;/a&gt; on the protests in Berkeley yesterday. " created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 20:25:16 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="The next programming &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/paulmillr/chokidar/issues/633&quot;&gt;question&lt;/a&gt; is about the Node &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/paulmillr/chokidar&quot;&gt;package&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=&quot;https://davidwalsh.name/node-watch-file&quot;&gt;watching&lt;/a&gt; local folders." created="Tue, 29 Aug 2017 01:32:43 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Sarah Larson's recaps of Game of Thrones episodes are the best. The one for the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/game-of-thrones-season-7-finale-recap-a-dragon-a-wolf-and-an-about-face&quot;&gt;season finale&lt;/a&gt; is no exception. &quot;At this moment, my neighbors learned what it sounds like in my apartment when they are watching the Super Bowl: loud, delirious bellowing and overjoyed profanity.&quot; Indeed. My neighbors as well. There is that one delicious moment in this episode that makes all the suffering if not worthwhile at least understandable. " created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 15:39:46 GMT" type="outline" image="http:///scripting.com/images/2017/08/28/littlefinger.png"/>
				<outline text="Two compelling lifestyle fantasies. An Italian &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.telegraph.co.uk/property/abroad/italian-ghost-town-sale-entire-village-available-less-price/&quot;&gt;ghost town&lt;/a&gt; you can buy for â‚¬250K, or a Joshua Tree &lt;a href=&quot;https://la.curbed.com/2014/1/31/10148482/breathtaking-joshua-tree-supervillain-lair-for-sale-for-first-time-1&quot;&gt;art house&lt;/a&gt; for $3 million. I used to have fantasies of living in places like these. To the person who lives in the town by themself or in the beautiful desert house far away from everything, show them a picture of an apartment building in NYC and point to one window and say &quot;you could live here&quot; and they'd get all excited about all the people they would see every day just by walking around. The grass is always greener on the other side, happiness is always just around the corner." created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 16:16:01 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="American-style, neo-Nazi and Nazi-sympathizer" created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 15:19:55 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="See Krugman's bit: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/28/opinion/fascism-arpaio-pardon-trump.html?smid=fb-share&amp;_r=1&quot;&gt;Fascism, American-style&lt;/a&gt;. I reject that. Fascism is fascism, whether it's in the US or Germany. Same thing. Adding an &lt;i&gt;American-style&lt;/i&gt; softens it. Makes it seem more acceptable. Oh it's like baseball, apple pie and Chevrolet. That must be better. " created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 15:20:18 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I also don't get when they call them neo-Nazis. What does the &quot;neo&quot; part mean? Something innovative and new? It's just Nazi. They wear 88 pins, they chant German Nazi slogans. If it sounds and looks like a Nazi, assume it's a Nazi. " created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 15:21:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="One more thing -- they call Trump a Nazi-sympathizer. Why be so generous. What distinguishes a sympathizer from an actual Nazi? We've been doing this with Trump at every stage, pretending he's not as bad as he clearly is." created="Mon, 28 Aug 2017 15:22:27 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 27" created="Sun, 27 Aug 2017 13:00:38 GMT" name="27">
				<outline text="I've started a &lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/burnerNews/&quot;&gt;news notebook&lt;/a&gt; for when Burning Man friends get home. " created="Sun, 27 Aug 2017 21:38:36 GMT" type="outline"/>
